OL,3,C'We're on a knife edge': What do
OL,4,Cpeople want from the Chancellor's
OL,5,CBudget?
OL,7,FElsewhere, suggestions that the freeze
OL,8,Fon fuel duty could be lifted, which
OL,9,Fhas been in place since 2011, has left
OL,10,Fsome taxi drivers feeling worried.
OL,12,F"If the fuel goes up, it means I make
OL,13,Fless money, because obviously I'm
OL,14,Fpaying more money for my fuel," said
OL,15,FPeter Badman, who has driven a taxi in
OL,16,FWeston for 20 years.
OL,18,FHe cannot understand why the
OL,19,FChancellor might change this now, but
OL,20,Fsaid it would make "a massive
OL,21,Fdifference" for him as a taxi driver.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/17
