OL,3,C'We're on a knife edge': What do
OL,4,Cpeople want from the Chancellor's
OL,5,CBudget?
OL,7,FOne cafe owner in Newquay believes the
OL,8,FChancellor should raise the VAT
OL,9,Fthreshold - the amount of money a
OL,10,Fcompany can take, before it has to pay
OL,11,FValue Added Tax. Claire Weiss said
OL,12,Fdoing this would mean she could retain
OL,13,Fall of her staff throughout the
OL,14,Fquieter winter months.
OL,16,FShe said: "If the VAT threshold was
OL,17,Fup, small businesses like ourselves
OL,18,Fwouldn't need to pay the VAT. So, it
OL,19,Fwould keep us open for more (of the)
OL,20,Fwinter you know and we wouldn't have
OL,21,Fto reduce the staff."
