OL,3,C'We're on a knife edge': What do
OL,4,Cpeople want from the Chancellor's
OL,5,CBudget?
OL,7,FIt's rumoured that Rachel Reeves will
OL,8,Fannounce a boost to the minimum wage
OL,9,Fby up to six per cent, which will be
OL,10,Fwelcome news for many employees but
OL,11,Fcould add to the financial woes for
OL,12,Fsome small businesses.
OL,14,FBut it is also believed that income
OL,15,Ftax thresholds will remain frozen,
OL,16,Fwhich means as salaries rise with
OL,17,Finflation, more people end up paying a
OL,18,Fhigher rate of tax. The Government has
OL,19,Falso confirmed that the #2 bus cap
OL,20,Fwill now be replaced with a #3 cap
OL,21,Finstead.
